{
  "page": "Last Lord Tarbeck",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The canonicity of the character presented in this article is currently unclear. They are not mentioned in the published works of <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>. However, they are mentioned in an expanded version of the Westerlands chapter from <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The World of Ice and Fire\">The World of Ice and Fire</a></i> that was published on Martin's website a few months before the book release date.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Until further information comes out, they should be considered a semi-canon character.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarbeck\" title=\"House Tarbeck\"><img alt=\"House Tarbeck.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/85/House_Tarbeck.svg/50px-House_Tarbeck.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/85/House_Tarbeck.svg/75px-House_Tarbeck.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/85/House_Tarbeck.svg/100px-House_Tarbeck.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Last Lord Tarbeck</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarbeck\" title=\"House Tarbeck\"><img alt=\"House Tarbeck.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/85/House_Tarbeck.svg/50px-House_Tarbeck.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/85/House_Tarbeck.svg/75px-House_Tarbeck.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/85/House_Tarbeck.svg/100px-House_Tarbeck.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Tarbeck_Hall\" title=\"Lord of Tarbeck Hall\">Lord of Tarbeck Hall</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarbeck\" title=\"House Tarbeck\">House Tarbeck</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_258_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">258&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/261_AC\" title=\"261 AC\">261&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Tarbeck_Hall\" title=\"Tarbeck Hall\">Tarbeck Hall</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> (presumed)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Mother</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_Tarbeck\" title=\"Rohanne Tarbeck\">Rohanne Tarbeck</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The \"<b>last Lord Tarbeck</b>\" is the semi-canonical designation for the three-year-old son of <a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_Tarbeck\" title=\"Rohanne Tarbeck\">Rohanne Tarbeck</a>. His given name is unknown.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Last_Lord_Tarbeck&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan Tarbeck</a> was executed during the <a href=\"/index.php/Reyne-Tarbeck_rebellion\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Reyne-Tarbeck rebellion\">Reyne-Tarbeck rebellion</a>, and his wife, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn</a>, and last surviving son, <a href=\"/index.php/Tion_Tarbeck\" title=\"Tion Tarbeck\">Tion the Red</a>, died during the assault on <a href=\"/index.php/Tarbeck_Hall\" title=\"Tarbeck Hall\">Tarbeck Hall</a> by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>. Ellyn's daughters, <a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_Tarbeck\" title=\"Rohanne Tarbeck\">Rohanne</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Cyrelle_Tarbeck\" title=\"Cyrelle Tarbeck\">Cyrelle</a>, were taken captive and forced to join the <a href=\"/index.php/Silent_sisters\" title=\"Silent sisters\">silent sisters</a>. Rohanne's husband had been executed alongside Walderan, and their three-year-old son disappeared during the assault. Although the boy was probably thrown down a well by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Amory_Lorch\" title=\"Amory Lorch\">Amory Lorch</a>, one of Tywin's <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a>, some stories claim the boy was smuggled to <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a> and became a bard popular for his sad ballads.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Last_Lord_Tarbeck&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Unknown<br />two wives</td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan</a><br /><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;Note 1&#93;</a></sup></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn<br />Reyne</a></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&